Spec out dry-type control power transformer with low heat loss
Verify capacitor configuration is switched with disconnect vs. Breaker switched

Visit site to determine installation and IP requirements
communicate with LDR mining on cost targets
Find permeability models for new mtl type
Determine Manufacturing requirements for new mtl
evaluate cost model for varying grain sizes
build Gantt chart for producing mtl

discussions.text: I just submitted the latest PLC code to the repository
Hey Peter, I'm having a heck of a time finding a transformer with the heat loss requirements we have
I am certain we will need to be creative building this transformer.  COTS is not going to cut it.
maybe we can use one of those collaborative sites and get a new design that will stay in-line with the customers expectations of cost
I will try to get some external bids for this work.
great, install them as soon as schedule permits
ok - after I run the service models for layout
Hey Peter, I'm having a heck of a time finding a transformer with the heat loss requirements we have
I am certain we will need to be creative building this transformer.  COTS is not going to cut it.
maybe we can use one of those collaborative sites and get some good designs
I'll take care of this.  Leave it to me
the new mtl we have developed should work in the transformer core
I agree, we just have to determine what mtl parameters we need
yes, and how they impact transformer performance and heat loss
OK, let me investigate; I'll look for a relevant magnetic permeability model
